"{\"uid\": \"dailyreckoning.com-the-cover-your-butt-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByJames Howard KunstlerPostedJuly 15, 2024  You can not deny that \\\"Joe Biden\\\" did hisgoodestThursday night facing down a half-dozen pre-selected reporters representing blob-adjacent news orgs such as Reuters and NPR at the post-NATO meetup damage-control event billed as a \\\"news conference.\\\"\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 67, \"end\": 70, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.9999473962901086, \"rank\": 5.190370138698976e-05, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\"}, {\"begin\": 71, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3172708827662394e-22, \"text\": \"Biden\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\"}, {\"begin\": 200, \"end\": 207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.6785602855293446e-30, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 212, \"end\": 215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3818662419015065e-33, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only a week after he declared himself to be the \\\"first Black woman vice president,\\\" he pivoted to correct the record, telling the D.C. press corps that he'd \\\"picked Vice President Trump to be vice president\\u2026\\\"  Everyone in the room saw that they were back in that mortifying scene inThe Caine Mutinywhen the confused and incompetent Captain Queeg reaches for the ball bearings in his pocket while the ship battles to stay afloat in a hurricane.\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 423, \"end\": 427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DC_Comics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.5581351956781824e-11, \"text\": \"D.C.\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DC_Comics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DC_Comics\"}, {\"begin\": 463, \"end\": 478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.9999999999754436, \"rank\": 2.4163062194823495e-11, \"text\": \"President Trump\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Caine_Mutiny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Captain Queeg\", \"types\": [\"Q571\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Caine_Mutiny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Caine_Mutiny\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the end of the harrowing hour, the old coot minced his way offstage, leaving the Democratic Party evermore sore perplexed as to how they might lever this burnt-out old husk out of the nomination they foolishly secured for him months ago.\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 978, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 822, \"end\": 838, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9994310418913448, \"rank\": 0.0005692820058613208, \"text\": \"Democratic Party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Am I being excessively partisan here?\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1017, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think so.\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think you'd have to be excessively partisan to watch \\\"Joe Biden's\\\" recent performances and conclude that he's somehow fit to be president.\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1093, \"end\": 1096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.9999473962901086, \"rank\": 5.190370138698976e-05, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\"}, {\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3172708827662394e-22, \"text\": \"Biden\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And for another four years?\", \"from\": 1179, \"to\": 1206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Seriously?\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1217, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"C'mon on, man!\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anyway, it ain't gonna be easy, as \\\"JB\\\" repeatedly insisted he had no intention of stepping aside, despite the forces mustering against him in Congress, the media and Hollywood.\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1377, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4854219330580334e-14, \"text\": \"Congress\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Congress\"}, {\"begin\": 1401, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.103098369955385e-25, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even CNN is turning on him.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1417, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.853037657557608e-33, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the #VeepTrump clip went viral on social media.\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1498, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So much for damage control.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moving on, you understand, do not you, what a fiasco the 75th anniversary D.C. NATO meetup itself was?\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1607, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9993239870101667, \"rank\": 0.0006764702923800671, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone in the room, including the key prime ministers and presidents, could sense how flimsy the alliance now appears, as led by our maundering near-zombie president.\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like \\\"Joe Biden,\\\" NATO's raison d'etre has been exposed as badly out of date and dangerously unhinged.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1903, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"score\": 0.9999473962901086, \"rank\": 5.190370138698976e-05, \"text\": \"Joe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Jonas\"}, {\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3172708827662394e-22, \"text\": \"Biden\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joe_Biden\"}, {\"begin\": 1819, \"end\": 1823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9993239870101667, \"rank\": 0.0006764702923800671, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg kicked things off declaring that Ukraine is on an \\\"irreversible\\\" path to NATO.\", \"from\": 1905, \"to\": 2018, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1939, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jens Stoltenberg\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jens_Stoltenberg\"}, {\"begin\": 1973, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0855217448621279e-22, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2013, \"end\": 2017, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9993239870101667, \"rank\": 0.0006764702923800671, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This controverts what everybody in NATO knows is Mr. Putin's clearest red line, and is therefore either a jape or a bit of recklessly provocative idiocy.\", \"from\": 2019, \"to\": 2172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9993239870101667, \"rank\": 0.0006764702923800671, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}, {\"begin\": 2072, \"end\": 2077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0848326178619029e-66, \"text\": \"Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only thing that's probably irreversible at this point is a Russian victory.\", \"from\": 2174, \"to\": 2253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2237, \"end\": 2244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9999866799530905, \"rank\": 1.3196079211421151e-05, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only real question is how much of Ukraine Russia will end up with.\", \"from\": 2254, \"to\": 2324, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2292, \"end\": 2299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0855217448621279e-22, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2300, \"end\": 2306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the more NATO insists upon Ukrainian membership, the more Russia will be determined to make sure it never happens.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2338, \"end\": 2342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9993239870101667, \"rank\": 0.0006764702923800671, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}, {\"begin\": 2356, \"end\": 2365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8207902391214754e-13, \"text\": \"Ukrainian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2387, \"end\": 2393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Maybe one day Ukraine will come to realize how they were just pawns of the U.S. and NATO to weaken Russia.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2551, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2459, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0855217448621279e-22, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\"}, {\"begin\": 2529, \"end\": 2533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"score\": 0.9993239870101667, \"rank\": 0.0006764702923800671, \"text\": \"NATO\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NATO\"}, {\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the way, that failed too.\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2580, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Russian army is bigger and more powerful than it was two years ago, while its economy is growing at a good clip.\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2585, \"end\": 2597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Armed_Forces\", \"score\": 0.9999999865149222, \"rank\": 1.3449495030432072e-08, \"text\": \"Russian army\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Armed_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russian_Armed_Forces\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Good job, guys.\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The truth of the matter is this: Following its transition out of the failed Soviet experiment 30 years ago, Russia was never a threat to its European neighbors.\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 2875, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2791, \"end\": 2797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.908003767391033e-15, \"text\": \"Soviet\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2823, \"end\": 2829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All the talk of Vladimir Putin seeking to reassemble the old USSR empire was knowingly false, as is the chatter now about Russia looking to invade Europe.\", \"from\": 2876, \"to\": 3030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2892, \"end\": 2906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.116590206036415e-58, \"text\": \"Vladimir Putin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vladimir_Putin\"}, {\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.783633591449809e-22, \"text\": \"USSR\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Soviet_Union\"}, {\"begin\": 2998, \"end\": 3004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What Russia actually sought was to be regarded, once again, as a normal European nation able to conduct normal business with the rest of Europe.\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3037, \"end\": 3043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The USA would not allow it.\", \"from\": 3177, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3181, \"end\": 3184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.142810086758503e-17, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Exactly why remains partially mysterious.\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3247, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Surely, post-1991, it was in the interest of U.S. military contractors to maintain their Cold War revenue streams.\", \"from\": 3248, \"to\": 3362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3293, \"end\": 3306, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9204038205523964e-19, \"text\": \"U.S. military\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To do that, a foreign hobgoblin had to be invoked - and perhaps China was not the best candidate, since it had begun manufacturing everything on sale in the Walmart - so Russia, with practically no export economy besides energy (which is considerable), was cast in that role.\", \"from\": 3363, \"to\": 3638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3427, \"end\": 3432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8806970130910958e-13, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 3533, \"end\": 3539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the politicians, too, surely liked creaming off their share of that military-industrial revenue stream, so they went along policywise, with figures like John McCain and Lindsey Graham leading the charge.\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3797, \"end\": 3808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McCain\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.8871785946179326e-12, \"text\": \"John McCain\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McCain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_McCain\"}, {\"begin\": 3813, \"end\": 3827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Graham\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lindsey Graham\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Graham\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lindsey_Graham\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the U.S. intel blob and State Department had darker motives, driven by an animus that has slowly revealed itself to be insane - just as the Democratic Party has turned obviously insane, adopting a playbook that could have been written by Franz Kafka.\", \"from\": 3849, \"to\": 4103, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3993, \"end\": 4009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9994310418913448, \"rank\": 0.0005692820058613208, \"text\": \"Democratic Party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Democratic_Party_of_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 4091, \"end\": 4102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Kafka\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Franz Kafka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Kafka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Kafka\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being likewise insane, the intel blob and the neocons at State harbored an unappeasable hatred toward Russia that, since the Soviet collapse, allowed no accommodation and gelled into a naked avarice for seizing the resources of Russia with a long-term plan to subvert the Russian state, break it up the way they broke up Serbia in the 1990s and direct a corporate looting operation of Russia's oil and mineral riches.\", \"from\": 4105, \"to\": 4522, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4207, \"end\": 4213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5990069751781746e-15, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/